# Creatio Security Rules

## Credential Safety

- NEVER expose credentials, API keys, or tokens in generated code
- NEVER log BPMCSRF tokens, session cookies, or `.ASPXAUTH` values
- Store secrets in environment variables or encrypted configuration ‚Äî not in source

## Data Access

- Prefer OData / DataService API over raw SQL for CRUD operations
- When SQL is required, use ONLY parameterized queries ‚Äî no string concatenation
- Validate and sanitize all user-supplied inputs before use in queries or API calls
- Apply least-privilege: request only the columns and rows needed

## Cross-Database SQL Compatibility

All SQL must work on BOTH MS SQL Server AND PostgreSQL:

| Use | Instead of |
|---|---|
| `CONCAT(a, b)` | `a + b` (MSSQL only) |
| `CURRENT_TIMESTAMP` | `GETDATE()` (MSSQL only) |
| `COALESCE(a, b)` | `ISNULL(a, b)` (MSSQL only) |
| `CAST(x AS TEXT)` | `CAST(x AS NVARCHAR)` (MSSQL only) |
| Standard `LIMIT/OFFSET` | `TOP N` (MSSQL only) |

- Avoid database-specific functions without providing a cross-DB alternative
- Test queries against both engines before deployment

## API Calls

- Always include BPMCSRF token in mutating requests (POST/PUT/DELETE)
- Use HTTPS for all Creatio endpoint communication
- Validate SSL certificates in production ‚Äî allow self-signed only in dev/test

## Security Audit Tools

When reviewing security posture or compliance of a Creatio instance, use the built-in audit tools:

### Quick Checks (SMB Tier)
- `creatio_audit_password_policy` ‚Äî NIST 800-63B / OWASP password benchmarks
- `creatio_audit_session_config` ‚Äî session timeout and CSRF enforcement
- `creatio_audit_auth_methods` ‚Äî Forms/LDAP/SSO detection (SSO via `SsoIdentityProvider` OData entity)
- `creatio_audit_security_headers` ‚Äî HTTP headers vs OWASP guidelines
- `creatio_audit_log_config` ‚Äî audit logging status and change tracking entity coverage (disabled by default in Creatio!)

### Enterprise Security Assessment
- `creatio_audit_rbac_model` ‚Äî full RBAC hierarchy with dangerous operation flags
- `creatio_audit_user_privileges` ‚Äî per-user effective permissions and risk score
- `creatio_audit_dormant_users` ‚Äî inactive users with active permissions
- `creatio_audit_separation_of_duties` ‚Äî toxic privilege combinations
- `creatio_audit_system_operations` ‚Äî dangerous operation grants
- `creatio_audit_external_exposure` ‚Äî portal/external role data exposure
- `creatio_audit_object_permissions` ‚Äî role √ó entity CRUD matrix
- `creatio_audit_column_permissions` ‚Äî column-level access restrictions
- `creatio_audit_api_surface` ‚Äî web services, processes, SQL script inventory
- `creatio_security_posture_score` ‚Äî weighted 0-100 score with A-F grade
- `creatio_compliance_evidence` ‚Äî SOC 2, GDPR, ISO 27001 control mapping
- `creatio_security_baseline` ‚Äî configuration baseline and drift detection

See `creatio-infosec.mdc` for detailed workflows and parameter reference.
